criteria.inclusion_criteria:
1. gave informed consent;
2. age less than 60 years;
3. diagnosed with CML, as confirmed by the presence of the Philadelphia (Ph) chromosome or the BCR-ABL fusion gene;
4. imatinib treatment failure.

criteria.exclusion_criteria:
1. severe irreversible comorbidity, such as renal, hepatic, pulmonary, or cardiac disease;
2. development of grade >=3 adverse events during 2nd TKIs therapy; 
3. pregnancy or lactation;
4. has T315I BCR-ABL kinase domain mutation.
